    "(ii) Masked language models (e.g., BERT [58], ERNIE [59]) mask some tokens in the text input, and aim to predict them based on the contextual information.",
    "For instance, LLM can calculate P(x i |x 1,..., x i-1, x i+1,..., x n), where x i is the masked token.",
    "Such models are more suitable to fill in the middle of the text (e.g., text classification tasks).Large Language Models for Databases Some initial attempts have been made to use large language models for database [60,61].",
    "DB-BERT [60] relies on the BERT model to summarize the database tuning manuals into rules.",
    "These rules can be used to enhance the configuration exploration procedure, since the RL model only selects rules to tune the database rather explores the whole space."
